        "management": "Tacrolimus: trough 8-12 ng/mL first 3 months, 5-10 ng/mL after. MMF: 500-1000 mg BID (dose reduce for leukopenia/GI toxicity). Prednisolone: 5-10 mg/day, taper off by 3-6 months in low-risk (steroid-sparing protocols). Ciclosporin alternative (2-4 h C2 monitoring preferred). Azathioprine 1-2 mg/kg/day as alternative to MMF."
